<p>i have programmed a website, for a client and now im developing a smartphone template. I used max-device-width as media query to separate smartphone and tablet. Everythng is working fine, but iphone 4 zooms the website. I dont know if i defined viewport wrong or is a bug? Website is:<a href="http://mksgmbh.com" rel="nofollow">http://mksgmbh.com</a>  I used following Viewport</p>  <pre><code>&lt;meta content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=0, target-densityDpi=device-dpi' name='viewport' /&gt; &lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" /&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I tried to set initial-scale to 1 but it doesnt work too.</p>